WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.376 --> 00:00:01.585
Donna?

2
00:00:02.920 --> 00:00:05.190
Previously on Elle...

3
00:00:05.214 --> 00:00:07.943
I wish we could wake up
from this nightmare. Bruiser.

4
00:00:07.967 --> 00:00:09.736
I just found
a way to get you home.

5
00:00:09.760 --> 00:00:12.614
Cosmo's doing
a semester-long internship in L.A.

6
00:00:12.638 --> 00:00:14.074
Tell me how to win. immediately.

7
00:00:14.098 --> 00:00:16.785
You just need to choose
from a few of these essay prompts.

8
00:00:16.809 --> 00:00:19.621
"When things get bad.
how would you stage your comeback?"

9
00:00:19.645 --> 00:00:21.623
I could write
about Donna's comeback.

10
00:00:21.647 --> 00:00:22.916
I can help her get rehired.

11
00:00:22.940 --> 00:00:24.751
Woods comma Elle?

12
00:00:24.775 --> 00:00:26.586
Hi. I'm Shannon Walker.

13
00:00:26.610 --> 00:00:30.006
Sorry. I forgot what it was like
to receive eye contact.

14
00:00:30.030 --> 00:00:31.883
Hey. Are you going to CarpetMart
on Saturday?

15
00:00:31.907 --> 00:00:33.719
Okay. what is CarpetMart?

16
00:00:33.743 --> 00:00:35.387
Why are you here with the chick
who got your mom fired?

17
00:00:35.411 --> 00:00:36.704
I'm not.

18
00:00:37.455 --> 00:00:39.891
-Since when is Donna your mom?
-Since birth.

19
00:00:39.915 --> 00:00:41.977
I haven't asked anyone
who their parents are in Seattle.

20
00:00:42.001 --> 00:00:44.688
Me going to our school
hinges on her working there.

21
00:00:44.712 --> 00:00:46.231
I-I don't want you to get kicked out.

22
00:00:46.255 --> 00:00:48.924
Then please. just give up.

23
00:00:51.260 --> 00:00:53.363
Everything just feels backwards here.

24
00:00:53.387 --> 00:00:55.449
-Okay.
-Hey. wait. what are you doing?

25
00:00:55.473 --> 00:00:57.016
Getting you out of your head!

26
00:01:01.562 --> 00:01:02.789
And who is that

27
00:01:02.813 --> 00:01:04.708
handsome young gentleman
who seems very concerned

28
00:01:04.732 --> 00:01:06.001
about your well-being?

29
00:01:06.025 --> 00:01:07.359
He's just a friend.

30
00:01:37.014 --> 00:01:38.682
Esther. you had an apple cider?

31
00:01:42.144 --> 00:01:43.246
Hi.

32
00:01:43.270 --> 00:01:45.832
Could I get a medium iced...

33
00:01:45.856 --> 00:01:47.083
Elle?

34
00:01:47.107 --> 00:01:49.068
-Hey.
-Donna?

35
00:01:50.820 --> 00:01:52.380
What happened to the fish market?

36
00:01:52.404 --> 00:01:55.175
This is my weekend gig.

37
00:01:55.199 --> 00:01:57.469
Why are you dressed for a sting operation?

38
00:01:57.493 --> 00:02:00.764
Oh. I'm trying to hide from a boy
who might go here.

39
00:02:00.788 --> 00:02:02.808
One time I saw him drinking
what I think was a coffee.

40
00:02:02.832 --> 00:02:04.518
but what am I supposed to do?

41
00:02:04.542 --> 00:02:07.270
This is the only coffee shop
I don't need my mom to drive me to.

42
00:02:07.294 --> 00:02:10.232
You are so brave. Ow! Gosh.

43
00:02:10.256 --> 00:02:15.070
Okay. so. this boy that you are avoiding.
is he dangerous somehow?

44
00:02:15.094 --> 00:02:16.220
Only emotionally.

45
00:02:16.887 --> 00:02:18.532
He's dating a girl
I've been desperate to befriend.

46
00:02:18.556 --> 00:02:20.492
I didn't realize it until too late.

47
00:02:20.516 --> 00:02:22.494
Oh. honey.

48
00:02:22.518 --> 00:02:23.912
Uh. Donna? You made

49
00:02:23.936 --> 00:02:26.081
another decapitated swan.

50
00:02:26.105 --> 00:02:28.649
I'm terrible at this.
I'll be right back.

51
00:02:31.277 --> 00:02:33.171
Elle?

52
00:02:33.195 --> 00:02:35.632
Shannon. You're here.

53
00:02:35.656 --> 00:02:37.008
Boo.

54
00:02:37.032 --> 00:02:40.095
You're both here.

55
00:02:40.119 --> 00:02:41.304
Together.

56
00:02:41.328 --> 00:02:43.139
Because you're a couple.

57
00:02:43.163 --> 00:02:47.143
Looking super strong and committed
this morning. I might add.

58
00:02:47.167 --> 00:02:48.752
Go us.

59
00:02:49.753 --> 00:02:51.857
Oh. actually.
you can settle an argument for us.

60
00:02:51.881 --> 00:02:54.693
We're splitting a bagel.
Which one's better?

61
00:02:54.717 --> 00:02:57.487
Blueberry or everything?

62
00:02:57.511 --> 00:02:59.447
You want me to choose?

63
00:02:59.471 --> 00:03:01.491
Between the-the two of you?

64
00:03:01.515 --> 00:03:03.726
-Mm-hmm.
-Mm-hmm.

65
00:03:05.269 --> 00:03:06.788
Sorry. Miles.

66
00:03:06.812 --> 00:03:08.832
Got to go blueberry. Girl code.

67
00:03:08.856 --> 00:03:11.126
Ah. I see.
So. you two are teaming up against me.

68
00:03:11.150 --> 00:03:13.169
Always.

69
00:03:13.193 --> 00:03:14.462
What can I get you?

70
00:03:14.486 --> 00:03:17.757
One blueberry bagel
with blueberry cream cheese.

71
00:03:17.781 --> 00:03:22.262
Goodie. a threesome. with Carmen Sandiego.

72
00:03:22.286 --> 00:03:23.805
Uh. can I get a croissant?

73
00:03:23.829 --> 00:03:26.391
Oh. that actually sounds good.
Can you make that two croissants?

74
00:03:26.415 --> 00:03:27.767
Got a blueberry bagel here.

75
00:03:27.791 --> 00:03:29.936
Uh. you guys can have it.

76
00:03:29.960 --> 00:03:31.670
Let's grab a table.

77
00:03:34.048 --> 00:03:36.526
And to think
we could've had everything together.

78
00:03:36.550 --> 00:03:37.903
That's...

79
00:03:37.927 --> 00:03:40.596
I don't know about "everything."

80
00:03:42.973 --> 00:03:44.975
Oh. you meant the-the bagel.

81
00:03:45.976 --> 00:03:47.203
Ignore me.

82
00:03:47.227 --> 00:03:50.064
Think I might have a hairline concussion
from that mosh pit.

83
00:03:51.732 --> 00:03:54.377
Oh. I-I think you got a...

84
00:03:54.401 --> 00:03:56.129
Mm.

85
00:03:56.153 --> 00:03:58.948
-Here. I'll...
-No! Don't.

86
00:04:03.452 --> 00:04:05.221
I mean. I want it there. It's mine.

87
00:04:05.245 --> 00:04:07.373
Okay. well. suit yourself.

88
00:04:08.374 --> 00:04:09.583
I have my own.

89
00:04:16.590 --> 00:04:17.984
I'm sure it wasn't that bad.

90
00:04:18.008 --> 00:04:20.987
We were practically rounding second base
in front of his girlfriend.

91
00:04:21.011 --> 00:04:22.614
Pause. Can we please discuss

92
00:04:22.638 --> 00:04:25.325
how epic it is
you have a genuine Seattle prospect?

93
00:04:25.349 --> 00:04:26.660
He's not a prospect. Madison.

94
00:04:26.684 --> 00:04:28.453
That's the point. I can't like him.

95
00:04:28.477 --> 00:04:30.121
Miles is with Shannon.

96
00:04:30.145 --> 00:04:32.791
and Shannon's basically
the coolest senior at Rainier West.

97
00:04:32.815 --> 00:04:34.626
They're the Brad and Gwyneth
of this dumb school.

98
00:04:34.650 --> 00:04:38.546
If they're so perfect. then why was Miles
totally flirting with you?

99
00:04:38.570 --> 00:04:41.132
Whatever.
I refuse to make another fatal mistake

100
00:04:41.156 --> 00:04:42.968
and turn my school against me again.

101
00:04:42.992 --> 00:04:44.511
Just go for it. Who cares?

102
00:04:44.535 --> 00:04:47.639
This will all be a distant memory
when you win the Cosmo contest anyway.

103
00:04:47.663 --> 00:04:49.057
Yeah. you're right.

104
00:04:49.081 --> 00:04:51.851
I just need to move back to L.A.
and get myself out of this mess.

105
00:04:51.875 --> 00:04:53.520
So we agree. Great.

106
00:04:53.544 --> 00:04:56.255
-I got to dip. Uh. later.
-Bye.

107
00:04:57.923 --> 00:04:59.901
Okay. Bruiser. no more boy talk.

108
00:04:59.925 --> 00:05:02.594
We need to focus
so we can get ourselves out of this mess.

109
00:05:04.096 --> 00:05:05.699
Essay number two.

110
00:05:05.723 --> 00:05:08.159
"Cosmo Girls are like cake:

111
00:05:08.183 --> 00:05:11.395
sweet. layered and a little bit naughty.

112
00:05:12.521 --> 00:05:15.375
But making a good first impression
is everything.

113
00:05:15.399 --> 00:05:18.086
If someone were to meet you
for the very first time.

114
00:05:18.110 --> 00:05:20.547
"what's one word they would use
to describe you?"

115
00:05:20.571 --> 00:05:22.382
Well. that's easy.

116
00:05:22.406 --> 00:05:24.450
It's obviously...

117
00:05:25.909 --> 00:05:27.703
Well. there are so many words.

118
00:05:29.204 --> 00:05:31.582
Elle Woods is stylish.

119
00:05:37.296 --> 00:05:39.006
Charitable.

120
00:05:42.301 --> 00:05:43.862
-♪ Caroline laughs ♪
-Confident.

121
00:05:43.886 --> 00:05:45.780
♪ And it's raining all day ♪

122
00:05:45.804 --> 00:05:49.492
♪ She loves to be one of the girls ♪

123
00:05:49.516 --> 00:05:52.120
♪ She lives in the place
in the side of our lives ♪

124
00:05:52.144 --> 00:05:53.621
Respectful.

125
00:05:53.645 --> 00:05:55.981
♪ Where nothing is ever put straight...

126
00:05:58.025 --> 00:06:00.069
This is actually kind of impossible.

127
00:06:01.070 --> 00:06:03.006
If I say I'm glamorous.

128
00:06:03.030 --> 00:06:04.710
are they gonna think
I'm not down-to-earth?

129
00:06:05.574 --> 00:06:08.011
If I pick "smart."
will they know I'm also fun?

130
00:06:08.035 --> 00:06:11.347
Should I say "motivated"? "Kind"?

131
00:06:11.371 --> 00:06:12.432
"Gemini"?

132
00:06:12.456 --> 00:06:14.601
"Vegetarian"?

133
00:06:14.625 --> 00:06:19.630
How could anyone possibly narrow down
Elle Woods to one single word?

134
00:06:20.631 --> 00:06:22.382
♪ I'm only happy when it rains ♪

135
00:06:24.134 --> 00:06:28.573
♪ I'm only happy when it's complicated ♪

136
00:06:28.597 --> 00:06:30.575
♪ And though I know you can't ♪

137
00:06:30.599 --> 00:06:32.577
♪ appreciate it ♪

138
00:06:32.601 --> 00:06:35.604
♪ I'm only happy when it rains ♪

139
00:06:36.688 --> 00:06:38.625
♪ Pour your ♪

140
00:06:38.649 --> 00:06:40.627
-♪ misery down ♪
-♪ Pour your misery ♪

141
00:06:40.651 --> 00:06:44.631
-♪ Pour your misery down on me ♪
-♪ down. pour your misery ♪

142
00:06:44.655 --> 00:06:48.635
-♪ Pour your misery down ♪
-♪ down. pour ♪

143
00:06:48.659 --> 00:06:52.639
♪ You can keep me company as long as ♪

144
00:06:52.663 --> 00:06:54.706
♪ you don't care ♪

145
00:06:56.750 --> 00:06:59.628
♪ I'm only happy when it rains ♪

146
00:07:00.754 --> 00:07:03.983
♪ You wanna hear about my new obsession? ♪

147
00:07:04.007 --> 00:07:05.985
♪ I'm riding high upon ♪

148
00:07:06.009 --> 00:07:08.446
♪ a deep depression ♪

149
00:07:08.470 --> 00:07:10.907
♪ I'm only happy when it rains ♪

150
00:07:10.931 --> 00:07:14.494
♪ Pour some misery down on me ♪

151
00:07:14.518 --> 00:07:17.437
♪ I'm only happy when it rains ♪

152
00:07:19.064 --> 00:07:20.416
I have no idea

153
00:07:20.440 --> 00:07:23.128
what this could be in reference to.

154
00:07:23.152 --> 00:07:27.298
Someone must have been
trying to write the word "SCOT."

155
00:07:27.322 --> 00:07:30.617
You know. a lot of people think
I'm fully Scottish...

156
00:07:32.327 --> 00:07:34.121
but I'm mostly Irish.

157
00:07:35.414 --> 00:07:38.167
Hey.
Way to ditch me at CarpetMart.

158
00:07:39.543 --> 00:07:41.646
I ditched you?

159
00:07:41.670 --> 00:07:43.565
I nearly suffered a head injury
as a result

160
00:07:43.589 --> 00:07:46.609
of that unsanctioned mosh pit
you dragged me into.

161
00:07:46.633 --> 00:07:48.361
It's a miracle I'm still alive.

162
00:07:48.385 --> 00:07:49.511
Well. then...

163
00:07:51.555 --> 00:07:55.392
let's not waste
your one wild and precious life.

164
00:07:59.771 --> 00:08:02.625
Know how you told me Principal Anderson
fudges facts on official paperwork?

165
00:08:02.649 --> 00:08:05.336
Dude left his last school
under "mysterious circumstances."

166
00:08:05.360 --> 00:08:07.797
It says "unknown." not "mysterious."

167
00:08:07.821 --> 00:08:10.699
You can't just change the word
to make your point more scandalous.

168
00:08:11.283 --> 00:08:12.635
Oh. Speaking of words.

169
00:08:12.659 --> 00:08:14.721
if you could describe me in one.
what would it be?

170
00:08:14.745 --> 00:08:18.016
Yeah. I'm not doing that. Anyway.
this article implies Anderson was fired.

171
00:08:18.040 --> 00:08:20.059
I knew that guy was shady.

172
00:08:20.083 --> 00:08:21.352
Not interested.

173
00:08:21.376 --> 00:08:23.271
-Elle. come on.
-Drop it.

174
00:08:23.295 --> 00:08:24.647
Seriously.

175
00:08:24.671 --> 00:08:26.441
Yo. Dustin.

176
00:08:26.465 --> 00:08:28.383
I got ideas for the flyers.

177
00:08:31.220 --> 00:08:32.846
Okay. let's see what you got.

178
00:08:54.993 --> 00:08:56.828
All right.

179
00:08:59.331 --> 00:09:00.749
How do I look?

180
00:09:04.586 --> 00:09:05.980
Religious.

181
00:09:06.004 --> 00:09:07.941
Well. I was actually going for "nice."
but "religious" works. too.

182
00:09:07.965 --> 00:09:09.776
Where did your neck go?

183
00:09:09.800 --> 00:09:11.819
The neck is the pedestal to the face.

184
00:09:11.843 --> 00:09:14.489
Well. I know turtlenecks haven't
traditionally been a part of my aesthetic.

185
00:09:14.513 --> 00:09:16.407
but maybe that was the wrong instinct.

186
00:09:16.431 --> 00:09:18.284
Maybe I'm a turtleneck person now.

187
00:09:18.308 --> 00:09:19.827
Turtleneck pers...

188
00:09:19.851 --> 00:09:20.954
-Wyatt?
-Hmm?

189
00:09:20.978 --> 00:09:23.081
I. um...

190
00:09:23.105 --> 00:09:26.942
inexplicably saw my Rolodex in your study.

191
00:09:28.944 --> 00:09:30.964
Mm. Can you go?

192
00:09:30.988 --> 00:09:33.240
Can you go?

193
00:09:34.283 --> 00:09:36.368
I will retrieve that for you.

194
00:09:38.787 --> 00:09:41.641
Honey. What's going on?

195
00:09:41.665 --> 00:09:43.333
Nothing.

196
00:09:44.334 --> 00:09:45.669
I just...

197
00:09:46.795 --> 00:09:49.649
Do you remember
when we were walking Bruiser in the park

198
00:09:49.673 --> 00:09:52.902
and some lady compared him to a dachshund?

199
00:09:52.926 --> 00:09:54.445
Of course. He was devastated.

200
00:09:54.469 --> 00:09:57.031
Yeah. well. now I know how he felt...

201
00:09:57.055 --> 00:09:58.765
Oh!

202
00:10:00.767 --> 00:10:03.621
Your housewarming invitations
feature a jump scare.

203
00:10:03.645 --> 00:10:06.082
Well. first impressions are everything.

204
00:10:06.106 --> 00:10:08.668
Your dad's mishap

205
00:10:08.692 --> 00:10:12.130
ran our family out of L.A.
and could have totally destroyed us.

206
00:10:12.154 --> 00:10:14.924
Thank goodness
we have our second chance in Seattle.

207
00:10:14.948 --> 00:10:17.760
But Elle. we can't afford
another embarrassment.

208
00:10:17.784 --> 00:10:20.513
Yeah. that would be so bad.

209
00:10:20.537 --> 00:10:24.142
Well. fortunately.
I've figured out that those two gay men

210
00:10:24.166 --> 00:10:29.314
that I've been seeing on my twice-daily
power walks live down the street.

211
00:10:29.338 --> 00:10:32.317
A well-dressed same-sex couple

212
00:10:32.341 --> 00:10:35.695
really increases
your party's social stock.

213
00:10:35.719 --> 00:10:38.740
And that just reminds me.
I need to give your father

214
00:10:38.764 --> 00:10:42.285
a few invites for his clients.

215
00:10:42.309 --> 00:10:45.955
The post-ops. obviously.

216
00:10:45.979 --> 00:10:47.898
And no judgment. but...

217
00:10:48.982 --> 00:10:50.793
Appearance is everything.

218
00:10:50.817 --> 00:10:53.153
-You're back already.
-Mm.

219
00:10:54.446 --> 00:10:55.840
What's that doing there?

220
00:10:55.864 --> 00:10:57.842
What?

221
00:10:57.866 --> 00:10:59.302
"Mike McCready"?

222
00:10:59.326 --> 00:11:01.346
Oh. a nice guy I met at a coffee shop.

223
00:11:01.370 --> 00:11:03.290
said he'd be open
for a little jam sesh sometime.

224
00:11:04.706 --> 00:11:07.560
That's just what the world needs:
more men with guitars.

225
00:11:07.584 --> 00:11:09.419
Well. I think it's great. Dad.

226
00:11:10.420 --> 00:11:11.731
Could I get a ride to school?

227
00:11:11.755 --> 00:11:13.256
-Yes.
-Let's do this. Oh.

228
00:11:16.051 --> 00:11:17.737
Yes. sh... you. no. you should take her.

229
00:11:17.761 --> 00:11:19.805
-I have envelopes to stuff.
-Great.

230
00:11:20.889 --> 00:11:22.200
-Bye. Mom.
-I love you.

231
00:11:22.224 --> 00:11:23.725
I love you.

232
00:11:36.822 --> 00:11:38.383
Bruiser?

233
00:11:38.407 --> 00:11:41.326
Honey. where are you? Come to Glam-ma.

234
00:11:44.913 --> 00:11:46.748
How's the brain injury?

235
00:11:47.874 --> 00:11:50.127
Did it turn you Amish?

236
00:11:50.710 --> 00:11:52.462
Modesty is nondenominational.

237
00:11:54.381 --> 00:11:58.277
I. um. I got your message
on our answering machine.

238
00:11:58.301 --> 00:12:00.780
I really appreciate you
dropping the Anderson stuff.

239
00:12:00.804 --> 00:12:02.323
Well. I meant it.

240
00:12:02.347 --> 00:12:03.783
I get that there are consequences.

241
00:12:03.807 --> 00:12:06.268
and I'd like to think of myself
as a loyal person.

242
00:12:07.269 --> 00:12:08.371
Loyal.

243
00:12:08.395 --> 00:12:10.790
-Adding that as a maybe.
-What?

244
00:12:10.814 --> 00:12:13.251
Hello. compatriots.

245
00:12:13.275 --> 00:12:15.955
Elle. I printed you a copy of this.
I don't think you read it fully.

246
00:12:16.653 --> 00:12:18.172
-Drop it.
-What is that?

247
00:12:18.196 --> 00:12:21.092
Oh. just Dustin being Dustin.

248
00:12:21.116 --> 00:12:22.510
Okay. everyone.

249
00:12:22.534 --> 00:12:26.496
Today. we are learning
about catalyzed reactions.

250
00:12:27.539 --> 00:12:29.600
You know what that means.

251
00:12:29.624 --> 00:12:31.644
Interactive science.

252
00:12:31.668 --> 00:12:34.689
Now. I have hydrogen peroxide
and different-colored soaps.

253
00:12:34.713 --> 00:12:37.358
When I add our catalyst.

254
00:12:37.382 --> 00:12:38.985
oxygen gets rapidly released.

255
00:12:39.009 --> 00:12:41.261
which aerates the soap. causing...

256
00:12:44.473 --> 00:12:46.117
Yes. Dustin.

257
00:12:46.141 --> 00:12:49.078
So. what you're saying is.
you needed a catalyst

258
00:12:49.102 --> 00:12:51.497
